    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-07-23T15:55:55+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-23T15:55:55+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-23T06:25:55Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-23T06:25:55Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A ridge of pressure system will build over South Australia this evening, with the associated high centre expected to lie over the Bight on Friday and Saturday. The high will move north over South Australia during Sunday, with a trough to build over the west of the State later Sunday ahead of a cold front to move over the Bight late Monday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW013" description="North West Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-07-23T15:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-24T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-23T05:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-23T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Winds south to southeasterly 20 to 30 km/h.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-07-24T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-25T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-23T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-24T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Winds southeasterly 20 to 30 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 3 and 7 with daytime temperatures reaching around 15.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:20am to 2:50pm, UV Index predicted to reach 5 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-07-25T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-26T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-24T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-25T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Areas of morning frost north of Marla. Winds east to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending south to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h in the early afternoon then becoming light in the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 2 and 5 with daytime temperatures reaching around 15.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-07-26T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-27T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-25T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-26T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Areas of morning frost west of Coober Pedy. The chance of morning fog south of Woomera. Light winds becoming northeast to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h during the morning then becoming light during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between zero and 6 with daytime temperatures reaching around 17.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-07-27T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-28T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-26T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-27T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. The chance of morning fog south of Woomera. Areas of morning frost north of Marla. Light winds becoming north to northwesterly 20 to 30 km/h during the morning then becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 1 and 5 with daytime temperatures reaching around 19.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
